jthread
------------------------------------------
The JThread package provides some classes to make use of threads easy on 
different platforms. The classes are actually rather simple wrappers 
around existing thread implementations.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20080523-1
  cygport-0.3.11-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gcc-g++-3.4.4-3
  libtool-2.2.2-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://research.edm.uhasselt.be/~jori/page/index.php?n=CS.Jthread

Canonical download:
  http://research.edm.uhasselt.be/jori/jthread/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack jthread-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./jthread-1.2.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/jthread-1.2.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/jthread-1.2.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjthread-devel-1.2.1-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libjthread1.2.1-1.2.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary packages:

(libjthread1.2.1)
  /usr/bin/cygjthread-1-2-1.dll
  /usr/share/doc/jthread-1.2.1/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/jthread-1.2.1/TODO

(libjthread-devel)
  /usr/include/jthread/jmutex.h
  /usr/include/jthread/jmutexautolock.h
  /usr/include/jthread/jthread.h
  /usr/lib/libjthread.a
  /usr/lib/libjthread.dll.a
  /usr/lib/libjthread.la
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/jthread.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

